    <bodyTop>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p>Queen Margaret University offers the BSc Hons Nursing pre registration programme leading to registration with NMC in Adult Nursing. Placement Pattern: <a rel="noopener" href="/media/8d8917bf2dd86eb/academic-calendar-2017-18-confirmed.pdf" target="_blank" title="Academic Calendar">Academic Year Calendar 2017-18</a></p>
<p>Policy for Supervision - Mentor Aide Memoir</p>
<p><a href="/media/8d8917bd3f1a8df/general-information-section-for-students-and-mentors-2012-2013.docx" title="General Information Section forStudents and Mentors 2012-2013"><strong>Placement Documentation</strong> </a></p>
<p>Year 1 ORA 2017-18 (MS Word Document)</p>
<p><a rel="noopener" href="/media/8d8917bf38e0710/nu2-cohort-handbook-2017-18.docx" target="_blank" title="Year 2 ORA 2018-18">Year 2 ORA 2017-18</a> (MS Word Document)</p>
<p><a rel="noopener" href="/media/8d8917bf400a4ba/nu3-cohort-handbook-2017-18.doc" target="_blank" title="Year 3 ORA 2017-18">Year 3 ORA 2017-18</a> (MS Word Document)</p>
<p>NMC Standards To Support Learning And Assessment In Practice</p>
<p><a href="/{localLink:umb://media/583fbed9eec84f21acf4bafd32dbd8dc}" title="Sign Off Mentor Update">Sign-Off Mentor update</a></p>
<p>Queen Margaret University, Napier University and Edinburgh University work collaboratively in the allocation of placements and support of mentors.</p>
<p><strong>Mentor Preparation </strong></p>
<p>According to the NMC all mentors should;</p>
<ul>
<li>Mentors must be on the same part /sub part of the NMC register as the students they assess unless in common foundation programme (1 st year of the programme).</li>
<li>All registrants who wish to become mentors after 1st September 2007 must have a minimum of 1 year full-time or equivalent part-time post registration experience.</li>
<li>All Mentors must be able to demonstrate that they have successfully completed an NMC approved mentor preparation programme or comparable preparation that has been accredited by a University as meeting the NMC requirements.</li>
<li>All Mentors must be recorded on a local database of mentors (PWA /E-Manager).</li>
<li>All Mentors will undergo a triennial review to demonstrate their fitness to continue to remain on the local database of mentors. Mentors MUST provide evidence that they have mentored at least <strong>2 students within the 3 years period</strong> and be able to demonstrate competence and currency as a result of a process of annual updating. The NMC recommend that some of this updating activity <strong>should have a face to face component</strong></li>
<li>Mentors must be available to supervise (either directly or indirectly) students at least 40% of their time in placement.</li>
<li>Mentors should ensure their assessments of students are both <strong>valid and reliable.</strong> (NMC requires Mentors/Sign-Off Mentors to collaborate with other mentors/ professionals to support their decision-making around student assessments.</li>
</ul>
<p>Please let us know if it can be improved in any way by contacting the programme leader <a href="mailto:LMcKinlay@qmu.ac.uk">Lesley McKinlay</a></p>
<p>Thank you for mentoring and supervising our students.</p>
<p><a href="mailto:LMcKinlay@qmu.ac.uk">Lesley McKinlay</a> Programme Leader BSc Hons Nursing</p>]]></Value>
